  "description": "This traditional Andalusian style villa offers fantastic accommodation and entertainment areas and is located 400m from Marbella’s finest beaches and restaurants. Elegant décor, various terraces, sea views and spacious bedrooms, this villa has it all! The entrance level is very spacious and airy thanks to the open plan living/dining/kitchen area. There is a beautiful indoor patio allowing natural light into all the rooms. The living area features a variety of sofas and seating areas and a fireplace for the winter evenings. The vast kitchen is fully equipped and has access to the terrace. There is a laundry room with a washing machine (no dryer). On this level there is also a double bedroom (210cm bed) with en-suite shower and access to the indoor patio, a separate Tv room and an independent “Wing” with 3 bedrooms (2 doubles (180) and 1 bunk bed), a bathroom (shower) and a kitchenette. The large, level garden has trees in one corner providing pleasant shade for the BBQ area. There is seating for 16. This area leads around to the very large pool (12 x 5,5m) and the vegetable/fruit garden. The terraces feature an array of sunbeds and parasols. Upstairs, there is the Master Bedroom with 210 double bed and en-suite with shower and jacuzzi bath and access to the upper terrace. There are a further 3 bedrooms (180cm beds), all with ensuite showers. The upper terrace has great sea views, a second built-in bbq/outdoor kitchen, dining area and lounge corner to enjoy sundowners watching the sun sets over the Mediterranean Sea. There is covered parking for 3 cars and space for further 2 cars, wifi and aircon. Villa Amfora is located in Elviria and is only 400m from the finest sand beaches of Marbella as well as some of its best beach restaurants and bars. Elviria is known for its charming centre as well as the wide selection of restaurants and bars. This centre is easily accessible by foot at just about 10-15 minutes and offers a choice of over 50 different restaurants, various supermarkets and many bars. On the beach you will also find plenty to do with various beach restaurants, bars and even the world-famous Nikki Beach. Furthermore, there is a place where you can do water sports so there’s plenty to do for everyone. Villa Amfora is very close to the Santa Maria Golf Course and a 10-minute car journey to the west will take you to Marbella centre where you can enjoy the Old Town. A 15-minute car journey to the east you will find the bustling town of Fuengirola which also offers a charming Old Town and various shopping centres and beautiful beaches. Please note that we welcome families and couples only, no groups under 30, and no hen or stag parties. Should you fall outside of this category but wish to book nonetheless, please send us an enquiry detailing a bit more about yourself and the group that you will be travelling with so we can request this for you. We look forward to welcoming you! Don’t forget to enquire about our concierge service!",
